name: Tukaram Bar and Restaurant

reviews.review_text: Always crowded, serves delicious meals, each item on the menu tastes awesome! Do visit this place if you want to explore the authentic Goan thali!

This restaurant is located in Mapusa however it is a bit far from Mapusa main market, rikshawala aur cab will charge around 200 to 250 rupees from Mapusa Market to reach this restaurant.

They are famous for their Malwani style fish and prawns thali and other seafood on the offering hence there is always a huge rush, expect some waiting time to get a place to sit.

Please note that there is no register or token system used for managing the waiting and at times people can break the queue which makes it frustrating for well mannered people.

Their thalis are well planned and there is a lot of items for 1 person. The 'sukka' and fried piece of fish or prrawn are very tasty. The fried Prawn are big in size and coated with Rawa masala, there is no option available to customise to non rava masala.

The shells and gravy are good too and goes well with steam rice they are served with. The yummy Sol Kadhi is brilliant to end your thali.

The food they serve is authentic Goan seafood and was delicious, with good quality and generous portions. It was definitely worth the money.
However, the service left a lot to be desired. We arrived when they were about to close, but they assured us they would still serve us. Instead, we ended up waiting for an hour, which was quite frustrating—we could have gone to another place if they had just been honest about being closed.

Additionally, the waiters were unprofessional, even jokingly offering beer to my four-year-old nephew. This kind of behavior is not acceptable.

The food is great, but the service needs serious attention.

description:
### Exploring Flavorful Delights at Tukaram Bar and Restaurant

Nestled in the Corlim Industrial Estate, **Tukaram Bar and Restaurant** beckons diners with its impressive **4.4-star** rating drawn from **642 reviews**. This culinary gem is especially revered for its **fish thali** and **seafood**, boasting a menu infused with authentic Goan flavors. Customers frequently mention the **barramundi** as well, showcasing the restaurant's dedication to quality and traditional preparation methods.

### Ambiance & Design

Upon entering Tukaram, guests are met with an inviting atmosphere characterized by vibrant décor that reflects the lively essence of coastal Goa. The lighting is warm and welcoming, enhancing the restaurant’s rustic charm. Photos shared by patrons capture a bustling environment filled with laughter and the clinking of glasses, highlighting the restaurant's casual yet vibrant vibe that attracts both locals and visitors alike.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

Tukaram’s menu is the star of the show. Reviewers rave about the **Malwani-style fish and prawns thali**, a hearty dish loaded with generous portions designed to satisfy the hungriest of diners. The **sukka**—a dry preparation of fish or prawns—is particularly praised, as are the **fried prawns** which are reportedly large and coated with a flavorful **Rawa** masala that adds a delightful crunch. A notable highlight in the thali is the **Sol Kadhi**, a refreshing drink that complements the rich flavors of the seafood.

The presentation of the food, captured beautifully in customer photographs, showcases vibrant colors and carefully arranged servings that reflect meticulous preparation. The thalis are not only a feast for the palate but also a treat for the eyes.

### Customer Experience & Service

While the food garners applause, the service at Tukaram shows room for improvement. Many diners shared experiences of long wait times, particularly during peak hours, hinting at the need for better management of queues. Reviewers noted that the absence of a reservation system can lead to frustrating experiences, especially for those keen on a timely dining experience. There were instances where staff interactions left something to be desired—such as unprofessional joking behavior towards young patrons—which have been flagged as an area that needs urgent attention.

### Popularity & Reviews

Tukaram's popularity is evident in the throng of customers, with many willing to travel from nearby Mapusa despite the distance. The buzz surrounding this restaurant on social media adds to its allure, as lovers of Goan cuisine continue to share their enthusiastic recommendations. The overwhelming positive sentiment surrounding the food, however, consistently overshadows the criticisms of service. 

### Utilizing Visual Content

The restaurant's lively atmosphere and delectable offerings are beautifully encapsulated in the customer-uploaded images. From the vibrant colors of the thali to the bustling scene of diners enjoying their meals, these visuals enhance the overall portrayal of the dining experience at Tukaram. A particular image captures an appealing spread of the seafood platter, with glistening prawns and expertly fried fish that clearly represent the restaurant's commitment to quality and freshness.

In summary, **Tukaram Bar and Restaurant** is a must-visit for anyone yearning to indulge in authentic Goan seafood. While the experience may be marred by relatively slow service during busy times, the culinary journey through each thali definitely leaves a lasting impression that makes the visit worthwhile. Whether you're a local or a visitor to the area, Tukaram offers a rich tapestry of flavors that captures the essence of Goa's coastal cuisine.
